<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">

<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">

 <head>

  <title>CSS Backgrounds and Borders Test: border-image-slice - percentages</title>

  <link rel="author" title="GÃ©rard Talbot" href="http://www.gtalbot.org/BrowserBugsSection/css21testsuite/" />
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-background/#the-border-image" title="6.7 Border Image Shorthand: the 'border-image' property" />
  <link rel="match" href="reference/ref-filled-green-100px-square.xht" />
  <meta name="flags" content="image" />
  <meta name="assert" content="Percentage values for border-image-slice are relative to the size of the image: the width of the image for the horizontal offsets, the height for vertical offsets. border-image-slice specifies inward offsets from the top, right, bottom, and left edges (in that order) of the image. In this test, the border-image-source has 5px of green at the top, 10px of green on the right, 15px of green at the bottom and 20px of green at the left; the remaing center is all red." />

  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
  div#test
  {
  border-color: red;
  border-style: solid;
  border-width: 15px 20px 35px 30px;
  border-image-source: url("support/outline-5px-10px-15px-20px-green.png");
  border-image-slice: 5% 10% 15% 20%; /* <number> Numbers represent pixels in the image */
  border-image-width: 15% 20% 35% 30%; /* 1 is default ; <number> Numbers represent multiples of the corresponding computed border-width; % is a percentage of height or width of border-box.*/
  border-image-outset: 0; /* 0 is default */
  border-image-repeat: repeat; /* stretch is default */

  /*
  Equivalent to this shorthand form:
  border-image: url("support/outline-5px-10px-15px-20px-green.png") 10% 15% 20% 25% / 15% 20% 35% 30% / 0 repeat; 
  */

  width: 50px;
  }

  img {vertical-align: top;}

  div#overlapped-red
  {
  background-color: red;
  bottom: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  position: relative;
  width: 100px;
  z-index: -1;
  }
  ]]></style>

 </head>

 <body>

  <p>Test passes if there is a filled green square and <strong>no red</strong>.</p>

  <div id="test"><img src="support/50x50-green.png" alt="Image download support must be enabled" /></div>

  <div id="overlapped-red"></div>

 </body>
</html>